      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ford Motor</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">Reuters</byline>
      <dateline>DEARBORN, Mich., April 9</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Ford Motor Company said the use of chlorofluorocarbons, a chemical compound suspected of causing depletion of the earth's ozone layer, will be eliminated from 90 percent of its manufacturing by the fourth quarter of 1992. The company said the use of chlorofluorocarbons in plastic foam for seats and interior trim will be eliminated before 1993.</p>
      </block>
